    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-07-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-07-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="370"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d370">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.0012/680</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-07-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 24, 1916, noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received July 25, 1.10 p.
                        m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4149. Think there is remote possibility that Germany might now sign Bryan
                    arbitration treaty. Shall I pursue matter? If so, advise matter be kept secret
                    so that if successful we may announce it suddenly. <persName
                        corresp="#p_BJHACV1">Bernstorff</persName> should not be informed as, if
                    treaty is signed, <pb facs="0567" n="281" xml:id="pg_281"/> think Chancellor
                    wants to do everything here. Of course suggest possibility Germany signing
                    treaty and then starting submarine war. Please inform <persName
                        corresp="#p_HEM1">Colonel House</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
